import requests

dsid='21d3e683-80a4-4d9b-bc89-ebb2df513dde'
# find by sampling all collections but only inspect ids in the returned list? Maybe datasets list doesn't include full info? Actually /collections has only ids etc.
cols=requests.get('https://api.cellxgene.cziscience.com/dp/v1/collections', timeout=20).json()['collections']
print('collections', len(cols))
found=None
for i,c in enumerate(cols):
    cid=c['id']
    detail=requests.get(f'https://api.cellxgene.cziscience.com/dp/v1/collections/{cid}', timeout=20).json()
    if any(d.get('id')==dsid for d in detail.get('datasets', [])):
        found=(cid, detail)
        break
    if (i+1)%50==0:
        print('checked', i+1)
print('found', found[0] if found else None)
